{{Infobox language |name=Chimila |nativename= |states=[[Colombia]] |region= |ethnicity=1,500 (2009)<ref name=e18/> |speakers=350 |date=2009 |ref=e18 |familycolor=American |fam1=[[Chibchan language|Chibchan]] |fam2=Arwako–Chimila |iso3=cbg |glotto=chim1309 |glottorefname=Chimila }}
'''Chimila''' (Shimizya) is a [[Chibchan language]] of [[Colombia]], spoken by the [[Chimila people|Chimila]]. At one time the [[Malibu languages]] were grouped with Chimila, before Chimila was considered a Chibchan language.
The "Cesar" name of the [[Cesar River]] and [[Cesar Department]] is an adaptation from the Chimila indigenous word ''Chet-tzar'' or ''Zazare'' ("calm water") into [[Spanish language|Spanish]], in reference to the [[Cesar River]].<ref>[http://www.lablaa.org/blaavirtual/musica/musabo/pag09-17.htm LABLAA - Luis Galvis: Don Gonzalo] {{es icon}}</ref>
''Guatapurí'' derives from the Chimila for "cold water", and provides the name of the [[Guatapurí River]].<ref>{{es icon}} Marcos Fidel Vega Seña (2005), ''[https://books.google.com/books?id=vp2UXZwctVEC&pg=PA14 Vallenato: Cultura y sentimiento]'', U. Cooperativa de Colombia. p14.</ref>
