==== Psalm 100 ==== This text of the 100th psalm is presented in the standardized non-Americanist Phonetic Notation literary orthography.<ref>{{Cite book|title=Jonn-à Yan Shìdun á Nu Jibu|last=|first=|publisher=Jibu Bible Translation Committee|year=1993|isbn=|location=Serti, Nigeria|pages=1}}</ref> {| style="white-space: wrap;" cellspacing="10" !Line !Original ![[International Phonetic Alphabet|IPA]] !Translation |- | rowspan="2" |[1] |{{lang|jib|Mpirká á byar á myann níng bidim pár,}} |{{IPA|/m͡piɾ.ká á bʲaɾ á mʲæ̃ níŋ bɨ.dim páɾ/}} | rowspan="2" |Shout to the Lord all the earth! |- |{{lang|jib|Abig dài swam yan Shinn Luyí ma pìkyinn àjwár.}} |{{IPA|/æ.bɨg dài sʷam yan ʃĩ lu.jí ma pì.kʲĩ à.ʒʷáɾ/}} |- | rowspan="2" |[2] |{{lang|jib|Aning wib Shinn Luyi ma pìkyinn mìmìg,}} |{{IPA|/an.iŋ wib ʃĩ lu.ji ma pì.kʲĩ mì.mìg/}} |Serve the Lord with joy. |- |{{lang|jib|Aning bi á pyànnwá ni ma jonn àjwár.}} |{{IPA|/an.iŋ bɨ á pʲàn.nʷá ni ma ʒõ à.ʒʷáɾ/}} |Come before him with a joyful shout! |- | rowspan="3" |[3] |{{lang|jib|Aning yì rag Shinn Luyí shi sig ni Shìdun.}} |{{IPA|/an.iŋ jì ɾag ʃĩ lu.jí ʃi sig nɨ ʃì.dun/}} |Acknowledge that the Lord is God. |- |{{lang|jib|Ku màm sig yi ínì, Yi shi sig í buwá, Yi í bìr mpìrká buwá.}} |{{IPA|/ku màm sɨg ji ɨ́nì – ji ʃi sɨg í bu.wá – ji í bìr m͡pìr.ká bu.wá/}} |He made us and we belong to him; |- |{{lang|jib|Ku ri pyag yi àràg barà, mpìr ri pyag bu apyagká buwá.}} |{{IPA|/ku ɾi pʲag ji àræ̀g ba.rà – m͡pìɾ ɾi pʲag bu apʲag.ká bu.wá/}} |We are his people, and the sheep of his pasture. |- | rowspan="3" |[4] |{{lang|jib|Aning kà bi á lu Shìdun ma jonn, Aning sa ya ku í soko.}} |{{IPA|/a.niŋ kà bi á lu ʃì.dun ma ʒõ, a.niŋ sa ja ku í so.ko/}} |Enter his gates with thanksgiving and his courts with praise. |- |{{lang|jib|Aning swam yan ku sai-à na kà á fir luwá ni.}} |{{IPA|/a.niŋ sʷam jan ku sai à næ kà á fiɾ lu.wá ni/}} | rowspan="2" |Thank him and bless his name, |- |{{lang|jib|Aning sa ya ku í soko, ma aning swam yan zìnnwá.}} |{{IPA|/a.niŋ sa yæ ku í so.ko – ma a.niŋ sʷam jan zìn.nʷá/}} |- | rowspan="2" |[5] |{{lang|jib|Shinn Luyí sàn hing, á zìm-à ku ri zìm yi níng, ma vinn fig á vinn bána.}} |{{IPA|/ʃĩ lu.jí sàn hɨŋ, á zɨ̀m à ku ɾi zìm ji nɨ́ŋ, ma vĩ fig á vĩ bǽ.næ/}} |for the Lord is good, and his gracious love stands forever. |- |{{lang|jib|Pìkyinn ǹsànwá shi sig hár kinn kinn.}} |{{IPA|/pɨ̀.kʲĩ ǹ.sàn.wá ʃi sɨg háɾ kĩ kĩ/}} |His faithfulness remains from generation to generation. |}
