a Dasa]] || 16th century || Vijayanagara Empire |- |[[Theatre]] (folk, [[Yakshagana]])|| ''Virata Parva''<ref name="virat">Ashton & Christie (1977), p21</ref><ref name="parva">Karanth (1997), p160</ref>|| Vishnu Varamballi || 1564 || None |- |[[Drama]] (social) || ''Mitravinda Govinda''<ref name="mitra">K. Marulasiddappa in Datta (1988), p1077</ref><ref name="mitra1">Mukherjee (1998), p235</ref> || Singaraya || 1680 || Mysore Kingdom |- |[[Biography]] || ''Kanthirava Narasaraja Vijaya''<ref name="kanth">Narasimhacharya (1988), p64</ref><ref name="kanthi1">Rice E.P. (1982), p89</ref>|| Govinda Vaidya || 1648 || Mysore Kingdom |- |[[History]] || ''Chikkadevaraja Vamshavali''<ref name="kanthi1"/><ref name="chikka">Narasimhacharya (1988), p23, p64</ref> || Tirumalarya II || 1698 || Mysore Kingdom |- |Grammar (modern) || ''Kannada grammar''<ref name="reeve"/> ||Rev. William Carrey || 1817 || [[Mysore Kingdom|Princely Mysore]] |- |Novel (Historical prose) || ''Mudramanjusha''<ref name="mudra">Murthy in K.M. George (1992), pp167-168</ref><ref name="manju">Kamath (1980) p280</ref> || Kempu Narayana || 1823 || Princely Mysore |- |Dictionary (modern) || ''Kannada-English Dictionary''<ref name="reeve">Kamath (1980), p279</ref> || Rev. W. Reeve || 1832 || Princely Mysore |- |Journalism (news) || ''Mangalura Samachara''<ref name="reeve"/><ref name="journ">Verlag in Wendt (2006), p159</ref> || [[Hermann Mögling]] || 1843 || [[Madras Presidency]] |- |Novel (modern Romance) || ''Saugandhika Parinaya''<ref name="sau">Narasimhacharya (1988), p26</ref><ref name="parinaya">Murthy in K.M. George (1992), pp167</ref> || [[Krishnaraja Wodeyar III]] || 1850 || Princely Mysore |- |Drama (early modern) || ''Shakuntala''<ref name="shakun">Kamath (1980), p282</ref><ref name="kuntala">Murthy in K.M. George (1992), pp169</ref> || C. Sehagiri Rao || 1869 || Princely Mysore |- |[[Ballad]] (native folk) || ''Sangoli Rayana Dange''<ref name="dange">Murthy in K.M. George (1992), pp168</ref><ref name="songoli">Prashad (2001), page xiii, chapter-Kannada folk epics, a profile</ref> || [[John Faithfull Fleet]] || 1874 || [[Bombay Presidency]] |- |Drama (mature modern) || ''Shurasena Charite'' (''[[Othello]]'')<ref name="shakun"/><ref name="othello">Guttal in Trivedi & Bartholomeusz (2006), p105</ref> || Basavappa Shastry || 1882 || Princely Mysore |- |Epic (early, prose) || ''Adbhuta Ramayana''<ref name="adhbuta">Murthy in K.M. George (1992), pp170</ref><ref name="nandalike">Krishnamoorthy & Mukhopadhyay (1991), p94</ref> ||Muddanna || 1885 || Princely Mysore |- |Mature Novel (Social) || ''Suryakantha''<ref name="kuntala"/><ref name="surya">Kamath (1980), p281</ref> || Lakshmana Gadagkar || 1892 || [[Bombay Presidency]] |- |Poem (modern) || ''English Geethagalu''<ref name="adhbuta"/><ref name="geete">Rao in Datta (1988), p1716</ref> || [[B. M. Srikantaiah]] || 1910 || Princely Mysore |- |Short Stories || ''Kelavu Sanna Kathegalu''<ref name="short">Murthy in K.M. George (1992), pp172</ref> ||[[Masti Venkatesh Iyengar|Masti]] || 1920 || Princely Mysore |- |Lyrical poems || ''Gari''<ref name="lyric">Murthy in K.M. George (1992), pp173</ref><ref name="gari1">Das (1995), p203</ref> || [[D. R. Bendre]] || 1936 || [[Bombay Presidency]] |- |Epic (modern) || ''Sri Ramayana Darshanam''<ref name="rama">Rao in Datta (1988), p1182</ref><ref name="mlnad">Murthy in K.M. George (1992), pp174</ref> || [[Kuvempu]] || 1949 || [[Mysore state]] |- |}
