'''Punjabiyat'''<ref name="Bhardwaj 2012">{{cite web | last=Bhardwaj | first=Ajay | title=The absence in Punjabiyat’s split universe | website=The Hindu | date=15 August 2012 | url=http://www.thehindu.com/opinion/lead/the-absence-in-punjabiyats-split-universe/article3772133.ece | accessdate=8 October 2015}}</ref><ref name="Priyanka KachhavaPriyanka Kachhava 2015">{{cite web | last=Priyanka KachhavaPriyanka Kachhava | first=TNN | title=Of Punjabiyat, quest to migrate and 'muted masculinity' | website=The Times of India | date=26 January 2015 | url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/nri/other-news/Of-Punjabiyat-quest-to-migrate-and-muted-masculinity/articleshow/46018873.cms | accessdate=8 October 2015}}</ref> (meaning Punjabi-ness)<ref>{{cite journal|last=Ayres|first=Alyssa|date=August 2008|title=Language, the Nation, and Symbolic Capital: The Case of Punjab|journal=The Journal of Asian Studies|publisher=The Association for Asian Studies, Inc.|volume=67|issue=3|pages=917–946|url=http://journals.cambridge.org/action/displayAbstract?fromPage=online&aid=1956644&fulltextType=RA&fileId=S0021911808001204|doi=10.1017/s0021911808001204}}</ref> is the name of the [[language revitalization]] movement of the [[Punjabi language]] and also the political, social and literary movement for preservation of [[Punjabi literature]], [[Punjabi language]] and [[Punjabi culture]]<ref name="The News International, Pakistan 2015">{{cite web | title=A labour of love and a battle cry for logical minds | website=The News International, Pakistan | date=8 October 2015 | url=http://www.thenews.com.pk/Todays-News-5-341109-A-labour-of-love-and-a-battle-cry-for-logical-minds | accessdate=8 October 2015}}</ref> by unity of [[Greater Punjab]].<ref name="Dogra 2013">{{cite web | last=Dogra | first=Chander Suta | title=‘Punjabiyat’ on a hilltop | website=The Hindu | date=26 October 2013 | url=http://www.thehindu.com/features/magazine/punjabiyat-on-a-hilltop/article5275645.ece | accessdate=8 October 2015}}</ref> In Pakistan, the goal of the movement is to stop the alleged state-sponsored suppression of Punjabi in favor of [[Urdu]],<ref name="Punjabiyyat 2015">{{cite web | last=Punjabiyyat | first=In the name of | title=The News on Sunday | website=TNS - The News on Sunday | date=15 February 2015 | url=http://tns.thenews.com.pk/in-the-name-of-punjabiyyat/ | accessdate=8 October 2015}}</ref> while in India the goal is to bring together the [[Sikh]] and [[Punjabi Hindus|Punjabi Hindu]] communities for speaking only [[Punjabi language]] in North Indian regions.<ref name="Singh 2015">{{cite web | last=Singh | first=IP | title=No Punjabi versus Hindi divide now | website=The Times of India | date=17 May 2015 | url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/india/No-Punjabi-versus-Hindi-divide-now/articleshow/47313787.cms | accessdate=8 October 2015}}</ref> Supporters in the [[Punjabi diaspora]] focus on the promotion of a shared cultural heritage.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://apnaorg.com/articles/preetam-singh/|title=The idea of Punjabiyat|last=Singh|first=Pritam|publisher=Academy of the Punjab in North America|accessdate=16 December 2011}}</ref>
==See also== *[[Punjabi Nationalism]] *[[Punjabi Language Movement]], [[Pakistan]] *[[Punjabi Suba movement]], [[India]] *[[Khalistan movement|Punjabi Sikh nationalist movement]]
